#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:5
msgid "Cross-Origin Storage (COS)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:8
msgid ""
"This feature is **experimental**. The underlying `Cross-Origin Storage "
"browser API <https://github.com/WICG/cross-origin-storage>`_ is a WICG "
"proposal that has not yet shipped in any browser. Emscripten's support is "
"provided as a progressive enhancement — the runtime falls back to the "
"standard ``fetch()`` path automatically when the browser does not expose the "
"API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:16
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:18
msgid ""
"The **Cross-Origin Storage (COS)** API is a proposed browser standard that "
"allows web applications on different origins to share large cached files, "
"identified by their cryptographic hashes. A file stored in COS by one site "
"can be retrieved by any other site using the same hash, eliminating "
"redundant downloads."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:24
msgid ""
"Emscripten's :ref:`CROSS_ORIGIN_STORAGE` flag integrates this into the "
"standard Wasm loading path. At build time, Emscripten computes the SHA-256 "
"hash of the final ``.wasm`` binary. At runtime, the generated JavaScript "
"tries to retrieve the compiled Wasm module from COS before falling back to a "
"normal network fetch. If the module is not yet in COS it is stored there "
"after download, making it available to other origins immediately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:32
msgid "When to use this flag"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:34
msgid ""
"COS only delivers a benefit when the ``.wasm`` binary is **byte-identical "
"across many different origins** — that is, a popular library whose compiled "
"binary is loaded by many independent sites. If every visitor to every site "
"downloads the exact same bytes, COS means they only download it once, ever."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:39
msgid "Good candidates are libraries or toolkits that are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:41
msgid "popular enough that many independent sites load the same binary,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:42
msgid "distributed as a stable, version-pinned ``.wasm`` file, and"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:43
msgid ""
"a **single primary** ``.wasm`` file (COS only covers the binary that "
"Emscripten compiles; any additional Wasm files loaded at runtime are not "
"covered)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:47
msgid ""
"**Do not** enable this flag for application-specific Wasm code built for "
"your own site. That binary is unique to you; no other origin will ever have "
"the same hash, so it will never get a COS cache hit. The normal HTTP cache "
"already handles per-origin caching efficiently."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:52
msgid ""
"The exception is a Wasm binary that you deploy across **multiple origins you "
"own** — for example, the same library shared between ``https://app.example."
"com`` and ``https://api.example.com``. In that case COS can eliminate the "
"redundant download between your own origins. Use :ref:"
"`CROSS_ORIGIN_STORAGE_ORIGINS` to restrict access to only those origins "
"rather than opening the cache entry to the world."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:60
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:62
msgid "Pass :ref:`CROSS_ORIGIN_STORAGE` at link time::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:67
msgid "Controlling which origins can read the cached file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:69
msgid ""
"The :ref:`CROSS_ORIGIN_STORAGE_ORIGINS` setting controls the ``origins`` "
"field passed to ``requestFileHandles()`` on the write (cache-miss) path.  It "
"has no effect on the read (cache-hit) path.  Three modes are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:73
msgid ""
"**Globally available** (default, no explicit setting needed) — any origin "
"can retrieve the file.  This is applied automatically when :ref:"
"`CROSS_ORIGIN_STORAGE` is used without specifying :ref:"
"`CROSS_ORIGIN_STORAGE_ORIGINS`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:82
msgid ""
"Use this for popular binaries loaded by many independent origins.  This is "
"the recommended mode for resources where global COS cache hits are expected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:85
msgid ""
"**Restricted to a specific set of origins** — only the listed origins can "
"retrieve the file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:94
msgid ""
"Use this for proprietary resources shared across a controlled set of related "
"sites.  Each entry must be a valid serialized HTTPS origin (scheme + host + "
"optional port, no path).  Mixing ``'*'`` with explicit origins is a **link-"
"time error**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:99
msgid ""
"**Same-site only** — pass an explicit empty list to omit the ``origins`` "
"field, making the file available only to same-site origins:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:108
msgid ""
"Use this for resources that should be shared across subdomains of a single "
"site but not beyond."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:112
msgid ""
"The COS spec defines a **visibility upgrade** rule: a resource's "
"availability can be widened but never narrowed.  If a resource is already "
"stored as globally available (``'*'``), any subsequent attempt to store it "
"with a more restrictive ``origins`` list is ignored by the browser."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:117
msgid ""
"This rule also has a security implication: because storing always requires "
"writing the actual bytes of the resource, no third party can probe the cache "
"to determine whether a restricted-origin entry was previously stored by "
"another origin.  A cache hit is only possible after an explicit write that "
"provided the content, so COS cannot be used as a timing oracle to detect the "
"presence of a resource that the probing origin cannot access."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:125
msgid "Requirements and restrictions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:127
msgid ""
"The flag emits a **warning** when the target environment does not include "
"the web (``-sENVIRONMENT=node``, ``-sENVIRONMENT=shell``): ``navigator."
"crossOriginStorage`` is a browser API and is never available in those "
"environments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:131
msgid ""
"It produces a **hard link-time error** in **SINGLE_FILE** mode (``-"
"sSINGLE_FILE``): the Wasm binary is embedded directly into the JS output and "
"has no standalone ``.wasm`` file or fetchable URL to key the hash on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:135
msgid ""
"It produces a **hard link-time error** with ``-sWASM_ASYNC_COMPILATION=0``: "
"the synchronous instantiation path bypasses ``instantiateAsync()`` entirely, "
"so the COS code can never be reached."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:138
msgid ""
"It covers **only the primary ``.wasm`` file**. Secondary files produced by "
"``-sSPLIT_MODULE`` (``.deferred.wasm``) and side modules loaded at runtime "
"via ``dlopen`` in ``-sMAIN_MODULE`` builds are fetched through the normal "
"network path and are not stored in or retrieved from COS. A warning is "
"emitted for both of these combinations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:143
msgid ""
"The COS API is a progressive enhancement. Browsers without the API continue "
"to load the Wasm module via the normal ``fetch()`` and ``WebAssembly."
"instantiateStreaming()`` path without any error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:148
msgid "How it works"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:151
msgid "Build time"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:153
msgid ""
"After all optimizations — including any ``wasm-opt`` passes run by Binaryen "
"— Emscripten reads the final ``.wasm`` binary and hashes it. The hash object "
"is embedded in the generated JavaScript glue as a build-time constant "
"(currently SHA-256)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:160
msgid ""
"No extra files are produced; the hash is part of the regular ``.js`` output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:163
msgid ""
"The hash is computed over the ``.wasm`` binary **as emcc produces it**, "
"after emcc's own internal Binaryen/``wasm-opt`` pass.  If your build "
"pipeline runs additional wasm post-processing tools *after* emcc exits — for "
"example, an external ``wasm-strip`` or ``wasm-opt`` invocation in a Makefile "
"or CI script — those tools change the binary and **invalidate the embedded "
"hash**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:170
msgid ""
"In that case you must recompute the hash of the final ``.wasm`` and patch "
"the value string in the generated ``.js`` yourself before shipping. A "
"minimal shell snippet for doing so (SHA-256):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:180
msgid ""
"On macOS, use ``shasum -a 256`` in place of ``sha256sum``, and install GNU "
"sed (``brew install gnu-sed``) or adapt the ``sed`` command for BSD sed "
"syntax."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:185
msgid "Runtime (web only)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:187
msgid "When the page loads, the generated JavaScript follows this logic:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:189
msgid ""
"**Feature detection** — check ``'crossOriginStorage' in navigator``. If the "
"API is absent, skip to the normal fetch path immediately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:192
msgid ""
"**Cache hit** — call ``navigator.crossOriginStorage."
"requestFileHandles([cosHash])``. If the handle is returned (the module is "
"already in COS), read it with ``handle.getFile()`` → ``.arrayBuffer()`` and "
"pass the bytes to ``WebAssembly.instantiate()``. Then invoke "
"``Module['onCOSCacheHit'](hash)`` if defined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:199
msgid ""
"**Cache miss** — if a ``NotFoundError`` is thrown, fetch the ``.wasm`` over "
"the network as usual, invoke ``Module['onCOSCacheMiss'](hash, url)`` if "
"defined, call ``WebAssembly.instantiate()`` immediately so the page loads "
"without delay, and then write the bytes into COS in the background (fire-and-"
"forget) using the ``origins`` value controlled by :ref:"
"`CROSS_ORIGIN_STORAGE_ORIGINS` (``'*'`` by default). Once the write "
"completes, invoke ``Module['onCOSStore'](hash)`` if defined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/CrossOriginStorage.rst:207
msgid ""
"**Fallback** — any unexpected error (``NotAllowedError`` from the browser, "
"network failure during the miss path, etc.) is logged with ``err()`` and the "
"runtime falls through to the standard streaming-instantiation path below. "
"The page always loads."
msgstr ""

